The '''Battle of Bia<U+0142>ystok'''  was a battle of the [[Polish-Soviet War]] that took place near [[Bia<U+0142>ystok]], [[Poland]] on August 22, 1920.
The battle was  between the 1st Infantry Regiment and withdrawing from the Warsaw remains of the [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic|RSFSR's]] [[Red Army]] [[Western Army (Russia)|16th Army]] group and 3rd Army troops in the city of Bialystok, complete breakdown Bolshevik forces <ref name="Szczepanski">{{pl icon}} {{cite web
| author =  Jakub Medek
| url = http://miasta.gazeta.pl/bialystok/1,35235,6953286,Czcijmy_Bitwe_Bialostocka.html
| title = Czcijmy Bitw<U+0119> Bia<U+0142>ostock<U+0105>
| date = 2009-08-21
| publisher = Gazeta.pl
| language = pl
|accessdate=October 13, 2011 }}</ref>. Ongoing fighting all day covered the entire city, whose individual parts repeatedly passed from hand to hand. During the battle, among others used several armored trains<ref>{{pl icon}} {{cite web
| author =  Jakub Medek
 | url = http://miasta.gazeta.pl/bialystok/1,78942,5615760,Zapomniany_bohater_zapomnianej_bitwy.html
 | title = Zapomniany bohater zapomnianej bitwy
 | publisher = Gazeta.pl
 | date = 2008-08-22
 | accessdate=October 13, 2011 
}}</ref>.

The Battle of Bia<U+0142>ystok memorial obelisk commemorates the battle and is located in the center of the street. The monument bears the name of the fallen during the battle including the commander of the 1st Battalion of the 1st Infantry Regiment Captain [[J<U+00F3>zef Marja<U+0144>ski]].

